<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1212,2012]" pageId="1" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,353,1328,1354]" pageId="1" pageNumber="17">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[362,463,1329,1354]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="17">Female:</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[480,547,1329,1355]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,272,1382,1406]" captionTargetBox="[236,1350,351,1358]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[236,1350,351,1358]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. External appearance of Perittia species. Fig. 1. P. mucronata 3 (Turkey: Aksehir region); Fig. 2. P. mucronata ♀ (Turkey: Aksehir region); Fig. 3. P. huemeri holotype 3 (Croatia); Fig. 4. P. huemeri ♀ (Hungary); Fig. 5. P. junnilaisella sp. n., 3 holotype; Fig. 6. P. junnilaisella sp. n., 3 paratype (Turkey: Aksehir region)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190274/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[531,547,1329,1355]" pageId="1" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 
<quantity box="[778,875,1329,1355]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
. Length of labial palpus 
<number box="[1177,1215,1329,1355]" pageId="1" pageNumber="17" value="1.2">1.2</number>
times diameter of head; pale ochreous, darker ochreous below. Head, neck tuft, scape and pedicel of antenna ochreous white, flagellum grey. Tegula and thorax ochreous. Legs pale ochreous with darker ochreous tibia and tarsal segments. Forewing ground colour white, sparsely irrorated with ochreous scales forming oval spot at mid wing length at fold; fringe ochreous white. Underside of forewing pale ochreous grey, fringe scales white. Hindwing pale grey above and below, fringe scales pale ochreous. 
<emphasis box="[935,1134,1523,1548]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="17">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1151,1240,1522,1548]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 - 24" captionStartId="11.[151,271,1447,1471]" captionTargetBox="[257,1323,197,1419]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[248,1340,197,1423]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 22 - 24. Female genitalia of Perittia species. Fig. 22. P. mucronata (Turkey: Aksehir region, L. Kaila prep. 3915); Fig. 23. P. huemeri (Hungary, L. Kaila prep. 4348); Fig. 24. P. r a v i d a sp. n. (Greece: Kos, L. Kaila prep. 4544)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190281/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[1206,1240,1522,1548]" pageId="1" pageNumber="17" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
): Papillae anales fused dorsodistally with non-elastic membrane; sickle-shaped in lateral projection, basally with long setae; membranous sac between papillae anales distoventrally, armed with coarse teeth. Apophyses posteriores slightly longer than papillae anales, straight and stout; apophyses anteriores curved, stout, less than 
<number box="[1318,1355,1638,1664]" pageId="1" pageNumber="17" value="0.5">0.5</number>
length of apophyses posteriores. Ostium bursae broad wine glass-shaped, width 
<number box="[1031,1083,1677,1703]" pageId="1" pageNumber="17" value="0.33">0.33</number>
of distance between bases of apophyses anteriores; dorsal wall spinose; depth of antrum 
<number box="[859,911,1716,1742]" pageId="1" pageNumber="17" value="0.33">0.33</number>
of width of ostium bursae, abruptly tapered into colliculum. Length of colliculum equal to depth of antrum; ductus seminalis narrow and tubular, joined cephalically to colliculum. Ductus bursae membranous, straight and tubular, 
<number box="[1077,1114,1793,1819]" pageId="1" pageNumber="17" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times length of apophyses posteriores. Corpus bursae rounded, medially sparsely covered by coarse internal spines; signum in caudal 
<number box="[151,202,1870,1896]" pageId="1" pageNumber="17" value="0.25">0.25</number>
of corpus bursae, elongate, dentate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
