<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="1" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1212,2012]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,152,294]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="1" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,325,1947,1973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</emphasis>
The female is newly described herein. External appearance and characteristics of male genitalia suggest that 
<taxonomicName box="[430,597,1987,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mucronata">
<emphasis box="[430,597,1987,2012]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="17">P. mucronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a close relative of 
<taxonomicName authority="Joannis" authorityName="Joannis" box="[874,1137,1986,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="echiella">
<emphasis box="[874,1007,1987,2012]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="17">P. echiella</emphasis>
(Joannis)
</taxonomicName>
. In female genitalia the membrane between ventral side of papillae anales is expanded as large sac with coarse teeth. A similarly armed sac occurs also in 
<taxonomicName box="[448,701,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="karadaghella">
<emphasis box="[448,701,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="18">Perittia karadaghella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[717,856,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="18">P. c a r l i n e l l a</emphasis>
(Walsingham) and 
<emphasis box="[1092,1194,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="18">P. r a v i d a</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1205,1272,190,216]" pageId="2" pageNumber="18">sp. n.</emphasis>
In females of other 
<taxonomicName box="[222,315,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[222,315,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="18">Perittia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species there is also an expanded sac, but it does not contain such coarse spines as in these species. Therefore, these characteristics do not unequivocally identify the closest relatives of 
<taxonomicName box="[1244,1399,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mucronata">
<emphasis box="[1244,1399,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="18">P. mucronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
